speech.blockquote:
The Select Sub-Committee on Transport, Tourism and Sport has completed its consideration of the following motion:That Dáil Éireann approves the terms of the following Agreements:-(i) Agreement on Air Transport between the European Community and its Member States, on the one part, and Canada, on the other part, a copy of which was laid before the Dáil Éireann on 11 December 2014;
(ii) Common Aviation Area Agreement between the European Union and its Member States, of the one part, and the Republic of Moldova, of the other part, a copy of which was laid before the Dáil Éireann on 11 December 2014;
(iii) Common Aviation Area Agreement between the European Union and its Member States, of the one part, and Georgia, of the other part, a copy of which was laid before Dáil Éireann on 7 November 2012; and
(iv) Euro Mediterranean Aviation Agreement between the European Union and its Member States, of the one part, and the Hashemite Kingdom of Jordan, on the other part, a copy of which was laid before Dáil Éireann on 12 December 2012.
